1
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:13,720
Looking at the report,

2
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:16,120
his immune rejection is very strong.

3
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,480
We must redo the tissue biopsy immediately,

4
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:20,879
and check the heart connections.

5
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:23,400
So you're saying,

6
00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:26,000
Gu Tiancheng's life is in danger at any moment?

7
00:01:26,879 --> 00:01:27,480
Understood.

8
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:28,040
Tiancheng.

9
00:01:29,919 --> 00:01:30,519
Uncle Duan.

10
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,400
Are you addicted to staying in the hospital?

11
00:01:34,319 --> 00:01:35,639
You just had a heart transplant,

12
00:01:35,639 --> 00:01:37,000
are you going to get a brain transplant next?

13
00:01:37,319 --> 00:01:37,919
This time,

14
00:01:37,919 --> 00:01:39,160
you actually hit the nail on the head.

15
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:40,160
Right now,

16
00:01:40,279 --> 00:01:42,000
I'm completely love-struck.

17
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:43,519
So lovey-dovey.

18
00:01:43,919 --> 00:01:44,879
It's unbearable.

19
00:01:45,639 --> 00:01:47,440
You were at death's door before,

20
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,559
and you cause trouble right after coming back.

21
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,360
Do you really think you've lived too long?

22
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:52,080
It really wasn't my fault this time.

23
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:53,279
I was framed by someone.

24
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,040
Alright, alright.

25
00:01:55,319 --> 00:01:56,760
Let's talk about something happy first.

26
00:01:59,559 --> 00:02:01,040
I want to reintroduce her to you.

27
00:02:01,639 --> 00:02:02,480
This here

28
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,599
is my girlfriend,

29
00:02:04,279 --> 00:02:05,040
Lin Jiaqi.

30
00:02:05,919 --> 00:02:06,839
From now on,

31
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,520
I'm going to date her properly,

32
00:02:09,119 --> 00:02:09,679
marry her,

33
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:10,880
and have babies.

34
00:02:11,279 --> 00:02:12,039
Come on.

35
00:02:12,039 --> 00:02:12,800
Why are you saying this?

36
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:13,360
What's wrong?

37
00:02:15,679 --> 00:02:16,240
Tiancheng,

38
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:19,240
come back for another checkup next week.

39
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:22,600
Isn't it a while before my regular checkup?

40
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,000
Why do I need a follow-up so soon?

41
00:02:24,279 --> 00:02:26,399
Who told you to get yourself injured?

42
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:30,039
Alright.

43
00:02:32,199 --> 00:02:32,839
I'll get going then.

44
00:02:36,679 --> 00:02:37,479
What do you want to eat?

45
00:02:39,039 --> 00:02:39,600
Something spicy.

46
00:02:40,119 --> 00:02:40,639
Let's go.

47
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:45,880
We're already at the company.

48
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:47,000
Alright, hurry up.

49
00:02:47,919 --> 00:02:48,520
Hurry.

50
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,320
Look at the security cameras.

51
00:02:50,759 --> 00:02:51,759
Hello.

52
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:53,039
What are you doing?

53
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,160
What about the cameras?

54
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:56,160
People eat, sleep, and date.

55
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:56,880
It's perfectly normal.

56
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:58,000
What's there to be shy about?

57
00:02:59,039 --> 00:03:00,039
I really can't deal with you.

58
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,240
Go to work.

59
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,440
Director Feng.

60
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:21,520
I have something to say to you.

61
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,399
Let's talk in your office.

62
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,160
Thanks for the gift.

63
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:49,039
The moment I took that hit and lay on the ground,

64
00:03:49,639 --> 00:03:51,240
I felt like I was enlightened.

65
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:54,119
What are you talking about?

66
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,279
If you hadn't gotten someone to hit me,

67
00:03:57,679 --> 00:03:59,440
how would Jiaqi have come back to me?

68
00:04:00,199 --> 00:04:01,320
So, putting it that way,

69
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,399
shouldn't I be thanking you?

70
00:04:03,839 --> 00:04:04,639
Gu Tiancheng,

71
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,839
just keep trying your hardest

72
00:04:06,839 --> 00:04:07,919
to talk tough in front of me.

73
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,720
The bond matures next week.

74
00:04:11,679 --> 00:04:13,399
There's no progress on the new product project.

75
00:04:13,679 --> 00:04:15,759
Let's see what money you'll use to pay the debt.

76
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,160
If you can't pay it back,

77
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,239
Feimanchi will have no choice but to go bankrupt.

78
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,279
If Feimanchi goes bankrupt,

79
00:04:23,119 --> 00:04:25,200
all the money you invested before

80
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:27,720
will become worthless paper.

81
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:29,239
Also,

82
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,600
if you're investigated

83
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,600
for illegal competition,

84
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,399
you might even become a criminal.

85
00:04:35,320 --> 00:04:36,559
Then I'd really like to see

86
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,559
how a penniless pauper like you

87
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:40,160
is going to love Lin Jiaqi.

88
00:04:41,079 --> 00:04:41,760
When that time comes,

89
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:45,200
will Lin Jiaqi still stay with someone

90
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:47,279
who is notorious and broke?

91
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,559
Are you that hungry?

92
00:04:53,559 --> 00:04:55,040
Why do you keep staring at the porridge?

93
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:56,799
It'll be ready in a bit.

94
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,119
Who said I was staring at the porridge?

95
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,160
I was looking at you.

96
00:05:03,399 --> 00:05:04,440
Why are you looking at me?

97
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:06,959
I think it's so magical.

98
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,640
What's so magical about it?

99
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:10,959
As long as you're by my side,

100
00:05:10,959 --> 00:05:12,119
I feel it's magical.

101
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,399
Where did you learn

102
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:17,600
all these weird things to say?

103
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,000
From TV dramas.

104
00:05:19,519 --> 00:05:20,279
I knew it.

105
00:05:21,559 --> 00:05:22,359
How could that be?

106
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,519
I haven't finished cooking the porridge yet.

107
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:27,119
This is your punishment.

108
00:05:27,359 --> 00:05:28,440
You have to hold my hand all the time.

109
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:29,519
Did you forget?

110
00:05:32,359 --> 00:05:34,720
No matter how busy we are with work in the future,

111
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:37,279
we'll set aside an hour

112
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,480
just to hold hands like this, okay?

113
00:05:43,239 --> 00:05:43,760
Senior,

114
00:05:44,359 --> 00:05:46,519
after my relentless checking of the surveillance footage

115
00:05:46,519 --> 00:05:48,079
and meticulous deduction,

116
00:05:48,359 --> 00:05:48,679
based on bold...

117
00:05:48,679 --> 00:05:49,320
All right, all right.

118
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,679
Get to the point.

119
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,359
I found the guy who attacked Mr. Gu.

120
00:05:55,239 --> 00:05:56,440
Good job, Xiao Mingming.

121
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:57,880
Of course.

122
00:05:58,519 --> 00:06:00,359
I heard this guy used to be in a gang.

123
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:01,519
Tan Feng.

124
00:06:01,959 --> 00:06:02,480
Take a look.

125
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,640
Is this the guy who led the attack on you?

126
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:06,000
Yes.

127
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:07,440
He's the one who led the guys to hit me.

128
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,679
I'd recognize him even if he turned to ashes.

129
00:06:10,239 --> 00:06:11,000
All right, Gao Ming.

130
00:06:11,760 --> 00:06:12,600
Send someone to arrest him immediately.

131
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:13,600
Understood.

132
00:06:51,519 --> 00:06:52,160
Officer Lin

133
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:53,079
My friend

134
00:06:53,519 --> 00:06:55,239
You're really asking for a beating.

135
00:06:55,679 --> 00:06:57,200
Did taking that beating make your brain

136
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,200
suddenly start working?

137
00:06:59,040 --> 00:06:59,959
I also think that hit from the club

138
00:06:59,959 --> 00:07:00,920
came at just the right time.

139
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:02,320
Go ahead.

140
00:07:03,559 --> 00:07:04,359
That watch

141
00:07:05,559 --> 00:07:06,559
might hold some clues.

142
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,600
Are you asking for another beating?

143
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:10,440
Are you addicted?

144
00:07:10,679 --> 00:07:12,160
You got my hopes up for nothing.

145
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,239
Bringing up the watch again.

146
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,440
Let's assume

147
00:07:15,359 --> 00:07:17,000
Du Zheng grabbed that watch.

148
00:07:19,119 --> 00:07:19,600
What?

149
00:07:20,119 --> 00:07:21,720
Wasn't Du Zheng hit by Feng Ziang?

150
00:07:22,839 --> 00:07:24,679
When he was lying on the ground dying,

151
00:07:25,239 --> 00:07:26,760
he begged Feng Ziang to save him.

152
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:27,720
And so,

153
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,320
while struggling,

154
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,119
he grabbed Feng Ziang's hand.

155
00:07:36,359 --> 00:07:37,040
Du Zheng

156
00:07:37,399 --> 00:07:38,880
used his bloodstained hand

157
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:40,000
to grab it.

158
00:07:40,559 --> 00:07:41,760
Which means that watch

159
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,720
has Du Zheng's blood on it.

160
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:44,519
Right.

161
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:46,920
Hurry and apply for a search warrant!

162
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:48,600
As long as we find that watch,

163
00:07:50,119 --> 00:07:51,119
wouldn't it all be over?

164
00:07:51,519 --> 00:07:52,040
Right?

165
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,600
I'm so incredibly smart.

166
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:55,640
Come on, high five!

167
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,359
Are you stupid?

168
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,239
Why don't you tell me

169
00:08:03,239 --> 00:08:04,600
how I can apply for a search warrant?

170
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:08,279
Yeah.

171
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:09,720
If I tell everyone

172
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,839
that I saw it in a dream,

173
00:08:11,559 --> 00:08:13,079
I'll be locked up in a mental hospital.

174
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:15,959
You're too smart, mental patient.

175
00:08:18,799 --> 00:08:19,679
Why don't you tell me

176
00:08:20,119 --> 00:08:21,839
how I can get my hands on that watch?

177
00:08:21,839 --> 00:08:23,399
How can I apply for a search warrant?

178
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:24,760
So, Officer Lin,

179
00:08:25,119 --> 00:08:26,320
this is up to you.

180
00:08:26,799 --> 00:08:27,640
What I can help you with

181
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,079
is only this much.

182
00:08:37,479 --> 00:08:38,119
It's for you.

183
00:08:38,119 --> 00:08:38,799
Take a look.

184
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,000
The watch

185
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,880
was carefully chosen by me.

186
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,239
It's one of a kind in the world.

187
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,640
It's really beautiful, Jiaqi.

188
00:08:55,479 --> 00:08:56,080
Uncle Duan.

189
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,479
The results should be fine, right?

190
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,440
I still have things to do at the company.

191
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,200
I'll get going now.

192
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:02,840
Tiancheng.

193
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:04,679
Stop right there.

194
00:09:06,159 --> 00:09:07,719
Have you been coughing a lot lately?

195
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:10,239
And feeling weak...

196
00:09:10,239 --> 00:09:11,000
Has it gotten worse?

197
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,080
Coughing?

198
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,039
Yes.

199
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:15,919
Weakness?

200
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,320
It's probably just because I'm too busy.

201
00:09:20,599 --> 00:09:22,719
Have you been getting frequent nosebleeds lately?

202
00:09:23,039 --> 00:09:24,119
And feeling dizzy?

203
00:09:26,719 --> 00:09:27,200
Oh, right.

204
00:09:27,799 --> 00:09:28,640
My cold this time...

205
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:29,880
It still hasn't gone away.

206
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,320
How about you prescribe me some more cold medicine?

207
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:33,599
Tiancheng.

208
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,719
This isn't a normal cough.

209
00:09:37,039 --> 00:09:37,919
And it's definitely not a cold.

210
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:39,080
Then...

211
00:09:40,159 --> 00:09:40,719
What's wrong with me?

212
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:41,919
These are...

213
00:09:42,919 --> 00:09:44,239
Symptoms of breathing difficulties.

214
00:09:45,159 --> 00:09:46,200
Breathing difficulties?

215
00:09:46,559 --> 00:09:47,159
Right now,

216
00:09:47,960 --> 00:09:49,479
Your condition is extremely dangerous.

217
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:50,599
So,

218
00:09:51,239 --> 00:09:52,000
You must immediately

219
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,440
Receive intensive treatment.

220
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:55,479
Uncle Duan.

221
00:09:55,479 --> 00:09:56,919
Stop using all this medical jargon with me.

222
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:58,080
I just want to know,

223
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,280
Is there something wrong with my body or not?

224
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:01,239
Judging from your vital signs,

225
00:10:02,039 --> 00:10:03,760
Your current heart function

226
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,440
Has already deteriorated significantly.

227
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,559
And your heart function will only get weaker.

228
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,400
If you ignore it,

229
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:10,840
You will very likely

230
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,559
Suddenly fall into a coma.

231
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,280
Followed by shock.

232
00:10:15,479 --> 00:10:17,000
You could die at any moment.

233
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,080
Do you understand?

234
00:10:32,599 --> 00:10:33,599
Where did you go?

235
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,200
You didn't answer my calls.

236
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,719
You weren't at home or at the company.

237
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:41,799
What's wrong?

238
00:10:42,599 --> 00:10:43,880
You don't look so good.

239
00:10:48,039 --> 00:10:49,599
Because the medicine is wearing off.

240
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,320
What do you mean the medicine is wearing off?

241
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:55,119
I'm like this because the medicine is wearing off.

242
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,159
Didn't you say

243
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:00,599
That I'm your medicine?

244
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,200
Not seeing me for a day

245
00:11:02,479 --> 00:11:03,520
Means the medicine is wearing off?

246
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:07,760
Alright, alright.

247
00:11:08,359 --> 00:11:09,159
Stop acting spoiled.

248
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:10,960
I'm right here, aren't I?

249
00:11:25,039 --> 00:11:27,159
What are you doing?

250
00:11:31,159 --> 00:11:31,960
From now on,

251
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,080
We should write down everything we think of,

252
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:33,960
And record it all.

253
00:11:34,479 --> 00:11:35,960
Then stick it in a visible place

254
00:11:36,119 --> 00:11:37,080
To constantly remind us.

255
00:11:45,159 --> 00:11:47,119
And if we can't do it in the future,

256
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:48,280
Will you punish me?

257
00:11:49,479 --> 00:11:50,679
Are you the only one allowed to punish me?

258
00:11:50,679 --> 00:11:52,039
Can't I punish you?

259
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,320
Didn't you say it before?

260
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:57,359
In the past,

261
00:11:57,359 --> 00:12:00,400
We always used being too busy with work as an excuse.

262
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,200
And we kept pushing back

263
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:04,039
The plans we made, over and over.

264
00:12:05,119 --> 00:12:08,119
And every time we'd say, "Next time, next time."

265
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,359
So,

266
00:12:10,719 --> 00:12:12,080
As long as we

267
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:12,799
Have time,

268
00:12:13,159 --> 00:12:15,200
No matter how busy or tired we are in the future,

269
00:12:16,039 --> 00:12:17,880
We must find time to travel.

270
00:12:18,559 --> 00:12:20,599
And do the things we want to do.

271
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,559
Writing it on here

272
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,000
Will constantly remind us,

273
00:12:24,119 --> 00:12:25,239
So we'll never forget.

274
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,239
So, from now on,

275
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:38,520
let's make a promise, okay?

276
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,880
No matter how busy and tired we are with work,

277
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,159
we'll try our best to complete

278
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:47,359
the things on these sticky notes.

279
00:12:48,119 --> 00:12:50,400
Then we'll eat instant noodles while fishing.

280
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,000
That's what I was thinking too.

281
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:57,119
So what should we do next?

282
00:13:01,599 --> 00:13:03,679
I want to dye Qi Shuai's hair.

283
00:13:04,559 --> 00:13:05,119
Sure.

284
00:13:05,359 --> 00:13:06,080
What color?

285
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,039
Jiaqi.

286
00:13:11,239 --> 00:13:13,799
I want to dye my hair pink.

287
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:16,000
